This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) using neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of auto-encoders and variational auto-encoders, which are popular techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hierarchical structures, which are commonly used in neural networks for tasks such as image recognition (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed method, which is related to the optimization of neural networks (cs.NE).
